members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Cursors to navigate through the result pages using `next` and `prev`. Returned if cursor paging is used.

members.name: hasNext
members.doc:
Indicates if there are more results after the current page.
If `true`, another page of results can be retrieved.
If `false`, this is the last page.

members.name: total
members.doc:
Total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging is used and the `tooManyToCount` flag is not set.
Might be empty if hard to calculate (for example, total number of sites)

members.name: billingServiceId
members.doc:
Service id in a premium billing system like `sbsServiceId`, `licenceId`, `bassId`. Same as `providerReferenceId` in Premium Assets API
Entities eligible for being returned:
`plans`, `domains`, `premium_apps`, `google_mailboxes`, `microsoft_mailboxes`

members.name: domainName
members.doc:
Domain name.
Entities eligible for being returned:
`domains`, `transferred_in_domains`, `google_mailboxes`, `microsoft_mailboxes`

members.name: invoiceId
members.doc:
Invoice id in SBS (premium billing system)
Entities eligible for being returned:
`plans`, `domains`, `premium_apps`, `google_mailboxes`, `microsoft_mailboxes`.
Search will fail if the invoice was issued for more than 500 services

members.name: metaSiteId
members.doc:
Id of a meta site or id of a meta site to which entities are connected.
Entities eligible for being returned:
`active_meta_sites`, `trashed_meta_sites`, `deleted_meta_sites`, `plans`, `domains`, `premium_apps`, `branded_apps`

members.name: msSearchTerm
members.doc:
Display name, meta site name or site url (domain name). Will return meta sites and entities connected to these meta sites
Entities eligible for being returned:
`active_meta_sites`, `branded_apps`

members.name: paging
members.doc: Cursor based paging. Will work for 1 returned entity type at a time if `cursor` is non-empty.

members.name: userId
members.doc: Id of the user for which search is performed

members.doc: The list of fields that are empty in the response due to errors on our side
